IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: FEED THE HUNGRY AND ASSIST OUR PARTNER AGENCIES FREE OF CHARGE.
IRS990.MissionDesc: FEED THE HUNGRY AND ASSIST OUR PARTNER AGENCIES FREE OF CHARGE.
IRS990.Desc: COASTAL HARVEST IS A FOOD BANK DISTRIBUTION CENTER LOCATED IN HOQUIAM, WASHINGTON. WE SOURCE AND DISTRIBUTE FOOD AND OTHER GOODS TO HUNGER RELIEF AGENCIES IN SEVEN SOUTHWEST WASHINGTON COUNTIES. WE CURRENTLY SERVICE 52 PROGRAMS INCLUDING FOOD PANTRIES, FEEDING PROGRAMS AND SENIOR CENTERS. OUR REACH ENCOMPASSES SIX NATIVE AMERICAN TRIBES AND OPERATES A MOBILE FOOD PANTRY IN TWO COMMUNITIES WITHOUT ACCESS TO HUNGER RELIEF PROGRAMS. COASTAL HARVEST ALSO CONTRIBUTES TOWARDS SEASONAL PROGRAMS, BACKPACK PROGRAMS AND SUMMER YOUTH PROGRAMS.COASTAL HARVEST PARTNERS WITH SEVERAL AGENCIES AND PROGRAMS TO PROCURE NUTRITIONAL VALUE FOOD FOR THOSE STRUGGLING WITH FOOD INSECURITY IN OUR COMMUNITIES. WE ARE MEMBERS OF THE INDEPENDENT FOOD DISTRIBUTION NETWORK (IFDN), WORKING COOPERATIVELY WITH NORTHWEST HARVEST (KING COUNTY) AND EMERGENCY FOOD NETWORK (PIERCE COUNTY) TO MAXIMIZE THE EFFICIENCY OF FOOD DELIVERY THROUGHOUT THE STATE. COASTAL HARVEST WORKS CLOSELY WITH THE WASHINGTON STATE DEPARTMENT OF AGRICULTURE TO ENSURE STATE AND FEDERAL FUNDS/COMMODITIES ARE DISPERSED EFFICIENTLY AND EFFECTIVELY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE AGENCY FILES INCOME TAX RETURNS IN THE U.S. FEDERAL JURISDICTION. THE AGENCY IS NO LONGER SUBJECT TO U.S. FEDERAL INCOME TAX EXAMINATIONS BY TAX AUTHORITIES FOR YEARS BEFORE JUNE 30, 2014. CURRENTLY, THERE IS NO EXAMINATION OR PENDING EXAMINATIONS WITH THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE (IRS). THE AGENCY ADOPTED THE PROVISIONS FOR FASB ASC 740-10 ON JULY 1, 2010. AS OF JUNE 30, 2018, THERE ARE NO TAX POSITIONS FOR WHICH THE DEDUCTIBILITY IS CERTAIN BUT FOR WHICH THERE IS UNCERTAINTY REGARDING THE TIMING OF SUCH DEDUCTIBILITY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COASTAL HARVEST MAINTAINS BILLS OF LADING FROM WAREHOUSES AND DOCUMENTS POUNDS OF FOOD DISTRIBUTED TO FOOD BANK SITES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE 990 WAS PRESENTED TO THE FINANCE COMMITTEE AND BOARD AT THEIR MONTHLY BOARD MEETING. THE CPA WHO PREPARED THE RETURN WAS AVAILABLE TO ANSWER ANY QUESTIONS THAT THE BOARD HAD.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COASTAL HARVEST REGULARLY MONITORS ALL INDIVIDUALS AND ORGANIZATIONS INVOLVED TO ENSURE CONFLICT OF INTEREST DOES NOT EXIST. TO ENFORCE COMPLIANCE, EMPLOYEES, BOARD MEMBERS, AND VOLUNTEERS ARE EXPECTED TO SIGN A CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY FOR UNDERSTANDING AND THEY ARE TO REPORT ANY ACTIVITY THAT MAY COME UP IN THE FUTURE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE PROCESS FOR DETERMINING COMPENSATION FOR TOP MANAGEMENT AND KEY EMPLOYEES IS DETERMINED BY THE BOARD. THEY COMPARE THE COMPENSATION TO THE MARKET WAGES AND BASE THE PAY ON QUALIFICATIONS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 18
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COASTAL HARVEST FORM 990 AND 1023 ARE AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST. OUR CONTACT INFORMATION IS LISTED ONLINE AS WELL AS THROUGHOUT THE COMMUNITY. WE ARE EAGER TO PROVIDE THE PUBLIC WITH ANY INFORMATION THAT IS REQUESTED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE GOVERNMENT DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST. THE CONTACT INFORMATION FOR COASTAL HARVEST IS LISTED ONLINE AS WELL AS THROUGHOUT THE COMMUNITY. WE ARE EAGER TO PROVIDE THE PUBLIC WITH ANY INFORMATION THAT IS REQUESTED.
